{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts"},"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Layouts","images":[{"identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"ic_folder_categories.png","type":"card"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components can be used for "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"layouts"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"level":3,"text":"Colored Surface","type":"heading","anchor":"Colored-Surface"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_coloredsurface_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mono"}]},{"type":"text","text":" suffix (for instance "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"text":"How it works","type":"heading","anchor":"How-it-works"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsUseMonochrome"},{"text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off"}]}]}]},{"level":4,"text":"How to use","type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-use"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"]},{"text":"Debuging contrast ratios","anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","type":"heading","level":4},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components like "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" can be used on "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Divider","anchor":"Divider","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"text":"How it works","anchor":"How-it-works","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_horizontaldivider_Orange"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"image","identifier":"component_verticaldivider_Orange"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSHorizontalDivider","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSVerticalDivider","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": to separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask)."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSDividerColor"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"How to use","anchor":"How-to-use","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSLink":{"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudslink","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSLink","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only or text with icon."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It also proposes layout to navigate forward or backward. The link can be displayed in "},{"code":"small","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" size."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","kind":"symbol","title":"OUDSLink","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSLink","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"component_coloredsurface_Orange":{"identifier":"comp